The paper proposes a new temporal logic that extends First-Order Linear-time Temporal Logic with Past, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of the logic in formal verification techniques such as model checking, which is a topic that falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of Satisfiability Modulo Theories (SMT), which is a topic that falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the encoding of the logic into equisatisfiable formulas, which is a topic that falls under the category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
